<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" ?>
<CustomMetadata
  xmlns="http://soap.sforce.com/2006/04/metadata"
  xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance"
  xmlns:xsd="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema"
>
    <label>FC - Billing Address Complete</label>
    <protected>false</protected>
    <values>
        <field>Record_Health_Check_Set__c</field>
        <value xsi:type="xsd:string">Account_Formula_Coverage</value>
    </values>
    <values>
        <field>CheckName__c</field>
        <value
      xsi:type="xsd:string"
    >Full Billing Address Is Complete (City, State, and Country)</value>
    </values>
    <values>
        <field>Tooltip__c</field>
        <value
      xsi:type="xsd:string"
    >Three required fields in a single rule using AND(). Extends the one-field pattern (`Account_DQ_BillingCity`) and two-field (`Account_FC_TwoFieldsAnd`) examples. The AND() wraps any number of NOT(ISBLANK()) checks — the rule fails if any field is missing. Admins can add or remove conditions using the same pattern.</value>
    </values>
    <values>
        <field>CheckMethod__c</field>
        <value xsi:type="xsd:string">Formula</value>
    </values>
    <values>
        <field>PassFailFormula__c</field>
        <value
      xsi:type="xsd:string"
    >AND(NOT(ISBLANK(BillingCity)), NOT(ISBLANK(BillingState)), NOT(ISBLANK(BillingCountry)))</value>
    </values>
    <values>
        <field>Severity__c</field>
        <value xsi:type="xsd:string">Error</value>
    </values>
    <values>
        <field>MessageWhenFailed__c</field>
        <value
      xsi:type="xsd:string"
    >{!Name} billing address is incomplete. City, State, and Country are all required.</value>
    </values>
    <values>
        <field>RunThisCheckWhen__c</field>
        <value xsi:type="xsd:string">Always</value>
    </values>
    <values>
        <field>RunOrder__c</field>
        <value xsi:type="xsd:double">15</value>
    </values>
    <values>
        <field>IsActive__c</field>
        <value xsi:type="xsd:boolean">true</value>
    </values>
</CustomMetadata>
